/agent/geminicli/gemini.go` (8 changes)**\\n   - Replaced regex-based path sanitization with proper SHA256 hashing\\n   - Changed `SanitizePathForGemini()` function to `GetProjectHash()` which uses SHA256 hashing (matching Gemini CLI's actual implementation)\\n   - Updated `ResolveSessionFile()` fallback to use Gemini's convention format: `session-<timestamp>-<id[:8]>.json` instead of just `<id>.json`\\n   - Updated `GetSessionDir()` to use the new `GetProjectHash()` function\\n   - Added `crypto/sha256` and `encoding/hex` imports; removed `regexp` import\\n\\n**2. `/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/gemini_test.go` (3 changes)**\\n   - Updated `TestResolveSessionFile` tests to expect Gemini-style filenames with `session-` prefix\\n   - Replaced `TestSanitizePathForGemini()` with `TestGetProjectHash()` that validates:\\n     - SHA256 determinism (same input → same output)\\n     - Correct 64-character hex string format\\n     - Different paths produce different hashes\\n\\n**3. `/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/checkpoint.go` (2 changes)**\\n   - Removed `SessionTranscriptPath` field from `WriteCommittedOptions` struct\\n   - Removed `TranscriptPath` field from `CommittedMetadata` struct\\n   - These fields previously stored the home-relative path to session transcripts\\n\\n**4. `/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go` (1 change)**\\n   - Removed assignment of `SessionTranscriptPath` when writing session metadata to the committed checkpoint\\n\\n**5. `/cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/resume_relocated_repo_test.go` (NEW FILE)**\\n   - **New integration test** validating the core fix: `TestE2E_ResumeInRelocatedRepo`\\n   - Verifies that:\\n     - A checkpoint created at one location works after the repo is moved\\n     - Session transcripts are written to the new location's session directory\\n     - Old location's session directory is NOT accessed\\n     - The resume command respects the current repo location, not stored paths\\n\\n**6. `/cmd/entire/cli/rewind.go` (1 change)**\\n   - Removed `resolveTranscriptPath()` helper function that was reading stored paths\\n\\n**7. `/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` (1 change)**\\n   - Removed `homeRelativePath()` helper function that converted absolute paths to home-relative format\\n\\n**8. `/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` (1 change)**\\n   - Removed `SessionTranscriptPath: homeRelativePath(state.TranscriptPath)` assignment when creating checkpoint metadata\\n\\n**9. `/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` (3 changes)**\\n   - **Removed `resolveTranscriptPathFromMetadata()` function** that expanded stored paths\\n   - **Removed `ResolveSessionFilePath()` function** that preferred stored paths\\n   - Updated `RestoreLogsOnly()` to compute transcript paths dynamically:\\n     - Always calls `agent.GetSessionDir(repoRoot)` with current repo location\\n     - Always calls `agent.ResolveSessionFile()` directly (not through stored state)\\n     - Removed fallback to stored transcript paths\\n   - Updated `classifySessionsForRestore()` similarly to use dynamic path resolution\\n\\n**10. `/cmd/entire/cli/transcript.go` (1 change)**\\n   - Moved and simplified `resolveTranscriptPath()` function from `rewind.go`\\n   - Now directly calls `agent.ResolveSessionFile()` instead of attempting to read stored paths\\n   - Uses current repo location for path computation\\n\\n### Key Architectural Change\\n\\n**Before:** Checkpoint metadata stored absolute paths to session transcripts → restoration failed if repo moved\\n**After:** Restoration computes paths dynamically from current repo location → works regardless of repository location\\n\\nThis change leverages agent-specific methods (`GetSessionDir()`, `ResolveSessionFile()`) to always compute the correct paths based on the **current** repository location, ensuring portability across machines and directory hierarchies.\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a3917ac (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usa