ways run `mise run test` before committing changes\\n   276→- Integration tests: run `mise run test:integration` when changing integration test code\\n   277→- Linting: always run `mise run lint` before committing changes\\n   278→- Code formatting: always run `mise run fmt` before committing changes\\n   279→- When adding new features, ensure they are well-tested and documented.\\n   280→- Always check for code duplication and refactor as needed.\\n   281→\\n   282→## Go Code Style\\n   283→- Write lint-compliant Go code on the first attempt. Before outputting Go code, mentally verify it passes `golangci-lint` (or your specific linter).\\n   284→- Follow standard Go idioms: proper error handling, no unused variables/imports, correct formatting (gofmt), meaningful names.\\n   285→- Handle all errors explicitly—don't leave them unchecked.\\n   286→- Reference `.golangci.yml` for enabled linters before writing Go code.\\n   287→\\n   288→## Accessibility\\n   289→\\n   290→The CLI supports an accessibility mode for users who rely on screen readers. This mode uses simpler text prompts instead of interactive TUI elements.\\n   291→\\n   292→### Environment Variable\\n   293→- `ACCESSIBLE=1` (or any non-empty value) enables accessibility mode\\n   294→- Users can set this in their shell profile (`.bashrc`, `.zshrc`) for persistent use\\n   295→\\n   296→### Implementation Guidelines\\n   297→\\n   298→When adding new interactive forms or prompts using `huh`:\\n   299→\\n   300→**In the `cli` package:**\\n   301→Use `NewAccessibleForm()` instead of `huh.NewForm()`:\\n   302→```go\\n   303→// Good - respects ACCESSIBLE env var\\n   304→form := NewAccessibleForm(\\n   305→    huh.NewGroup(\\n   306→        huh.NewSelect[string]().\\n   307→            Title(\\\"Choose an option\\\").\\n   308→            Options(...).\\n   309→            Value(&choice),\\n   310→    ),\\n   311→)\\n   312→\\n   313→// Bad - ignores accessibility setting\\n   314→form := huh.NewForm(...)\\n